extends ../../layout

block content
  h2 Other controls
  
  section
    h3 Task 1
    blockquote(cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Test_your_skills:_Other_controls#Other_controls_1")
      p In our first "other controls" assessment, we'll get you to create a multi-line text input.
      ol 
        li Create a basic multi-line text input.
        li Associate it semantically with the provided "Comment" label.
        li Give the input 35 columns, and 10 rows of space in which to add comments.
        li Give the comments a maximum length of 100 characters.
    form
      h2 Enter your comment
      ul 
        li 
          label(for="name") Name:
          input#name(type="text", name="name")
        li 
          label(for="comment") Comment:
          textarea#comment(name="comment", cols="35", rows="10", maxlength="100")
        li 
          button(type="submit") Submit comment

  section
    h3 Task 2
    blockquote(cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Test_your_skills:_Other_controls#Other_controls_2")
      p Now it's time to have a go at implementing a drop-down select menu, to allow a user to pick their favourite food from the choices provided.
      ol 
        li Create your basic select box structure.
        li Associate it semantically with the provided "Food" label.
        li Inside the list, split the choices up into 2 subgroups â€” "mains" and "snacks".
    form 
      ul 
        li
          label(for="food") Pick your favorite food:
          select#food(name="food")
            optgroup(label="mains")
              option(value="") Salad
              option(value="") Curry
              option(value="") Pizza
              option(value="") Fajitas
            optgroup(label="snacks")
              option(value="") Biscuits
              option(value="") Crisps
              option(value="") Fruit
              option(value="") Breadsticks
        li
          button(type="submit") Submit

  section
    h3 Task 3
    blockquote(cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Test_your_skills:_Other_controls#Other_controls_3")
      p In our final task of this set, we start with much the same list of food choices. However, this time we want to do things differently:
      ol 
        li Create a basic text input that is semantically associated with the provided label.
        li Put the food choices into a list that can be associated with a form input.
        li Associate the list with your text input, so that when you type characters, any of the list options that match the character sequence are given in a dropdown list as autocomplete suggestions.
    form 
      ul 
        li 
          label(for="ffood") Enter your favorite food:
          input#ffood(type="text", name="food" list="foodlist")
          datalist#foodlist
            option Salad
            option Curry
            option Pizza
            option Fajitas
            option Biscuits
            option Crisps
            option Fruit
            option Breadsticks
        li 
          button(type="submit") Submit choice